'''Alto Pativilca–Alto Marañón–Alto Huallaga Quechua''' (abbreviated '''AP–AM–AH''') is a [[dialect cluster]] of [[Quechua languages]] spoken in the Peruvian provinces of [[Huánuco Province|Huánuco]], [[Lauricocha Province|Lauricocha]], [[Cajatambo Province|Cajatambo]] and neighboring areas. The best-known dialect within the Huánuco cluster is [[Huallaga Quechua]].
